rComments: Very good lecturer! It was the only class I enjoyed going to. The SP is long,  but they are very lenient on grading. The final was actually kinda hard and dropped me to an A- so watch out for that. Overall, he curves the class around an A-/B+, so you're good there, but really take this class because you learn things you actually want to learn.

Take notes on Young's lecture, not his PowerPoint slides. Most test questions come from something he said but did not have written on a slide. Group project is graded generously. Material is presented in a very pleasant way. Ask questions! Overall I liked the class, but the tests demanded insanely specific info that he only mentioned once in class.

Probably the best teacher i've ever had. If you don't want to be convinced to switch to construction management then don't take this class!! His lectures are very engaging, and interesting. And he makes it very easy for students to succeed.
